<div class="card-header">
<h1>Homestyle Potatoes and Sausag</h1></div>
<p>Growing up, I would always make breakfast for my younger siblings.They were all so picky and they never wanted anything I prepared. That changed the day I made my famous homestyle potatoes and sausage. 
I usually eat this meal as a quick breakdfast option. I am currently a pescatarian so I don't eat the sausage but I still prepare it for my siblings. Today, I will walk you through my infamous recipie. </p>
  
  <center> <h2 class="card-title"> Ingredients</h2> </center>
<ul>
 <li class="list-group-item">3 medium sized potatoes</li> 
    <li class="list-group-item">1 onion</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">2 medium sized tomatoes </li>
   <li class="list-group-item">1 large green pepper </li>
   <li class="list-group-item"> 2 tps of red pepper flakes</li>
   <li class="list-group-item">2 cloves of garlic </li>
    <li class="list-group-item">2 tps of salt</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">2 tsp of pepper</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">13oz Turkey Sausage</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">3/4 cup of vegetable oil</li>
</ul>
  <center> <h2 class="card-title">What to Do!</h2> </center>
<ol>
    <li>First, rinse all of your vegetables</li>
    <li>Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes</li>
    <li>Place into a strainer and strain now cut potatoes</li>
    <li >Season with 1 tps of salt</li>
    <li>Place frying pan on stove with 3/4 cups of oil over medium heat</li>
    <li>While the oil heats, slice the turkey sausage into small circles</li> 
    <li>Place potatoes into heated oil</li>
    <li>Dice green pepper, garlic, onion, and tomatoes into small cubes</li>  
    <li>Continuously mix potatoes,making sure that each side is cooked</li> 
   <li>Fry for about 5-10 minutes or until golden brown</li> 
   <li>Reduce heat, remove potatoes from pan and drain oil</li>  
    <li> Leaving only a little oil remaning in the pan and place back on stove over medium heat adding add the garlic and 1 tsp of salt</li> 
   <li>Satuee for about a minute and add sausage</li> 
    <li>Cook sausage for about 7 minutes almost fully cooked</li>  
    <li> Add onion, tomatoes, and bell pepper to the pan</li>
  <li>Mix continuously </li>
  <li> Cook until vegetables are tender and sausage if fully cooked</li>
  <li>Season with red pepper flakes and pepper </li>
  <li> Place over low heat to let the season cook in for about 3 minutes</li>
  <li> Reduce heat, Plate and Serve</li>
  
    <li>Enjoy the meal!</li>
    </ol>
    
